replies.bodyText:
It's relatively easy to do so by implementing a custom ApolloInterceptorFactory:
class OnlyPersistQueriesInterceptor: ApolloInterceptorFactory {
    override fun newInterceptor(logger: Logger, operation: Operation<?, ?, ?>) = if (operation is Query) {
         ApolloAutoPersistedOperationInterceptor(logger, false);
    } else {
       null
    }
}
But it might be easier to add more params to the Factory. Something like this:
Factory(boolean useHttpGetForQueries, boolean persistQueries, boolean persistMutations)
?
The useHttpGetForQueries feels a bit asymmetrical though. Maybe it is the one that should be left out instead?
